.TH throw-items
.SH NAME
throw-items - client request for removing items from the object inventory.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The throw-items request is used by the client to remove items from the object inventory.
.br
Object to remove items from, need to be under client control.
.br
This request contains ID and serial value of object and list of items to remove.
.br
List contains a map of the item IDs as keys and serial values of specific items to remove from the object inventory.
.br
The removed items will be transfered to the area object(obLoot1) spawned on the same position as the current position of the request object.
.br
Despawn time of the loot object can be configured with loot-despawn-time config value(5 sec by default).
.SH JSON EXAMPLE
.nf
{
  "throw-items": [
    {
      "object": "char1",
      "object-serial": "0",
      "items": {
        "item1": [
          "0"
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
